标题：车辆、车（cart, wagon）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">经文出处</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：גַּלְגַּל</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：galgal)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:24\">EZK 23:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:10\">EZK 26:10</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：עֲגָלָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：‘agalah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:19\">GEN 45:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:21\">GEN 45:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:27\">GEN 45:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:5\">GEN 46:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:3\">NUM 7:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:3\">NUM 7:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:6\">NUM 7:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:7\">NUM 7:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:8\">NUM 7:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:7\">1SA 6:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:7\">1SA 6:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:8\">1SA 6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:10\">1SA 6:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:11\">1SA 6:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:14\">1SA 6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:14\">1SA 6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:3\">2SA 6:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:3\">2SA 6:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr13:7\">1CH 13:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr13:7\">1CH 13:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps46:10\">PSA 46:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:18\">ISA 5:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:27\">ISA 28:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:28\">ISA 28:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:13\">AMO 2:13</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：צָב, עֲגָלָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：tsav, ‘egloth tsav)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:3\">NUM 7:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:3\">NUM 7:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:20\">ISA 66:20</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：ἅμαξα</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：hamaxa)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jdt15:11\">JDT 15:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir33:5\">SIR 33:5</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：καρρον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：karron)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Esd5:53\">1ES 5:53</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：ῥέδη</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：rhedē)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:13\">REV 18:13</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述和用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/UBS-0035_wagon_model.jpg\" alt=\"马车模型\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">马车模型 (© Deutsche Bibelgesellschaft, Stuttgart by United Bible Societies)</figcaption></figure>车辆是一种用于旅行或运输货物的两轮或四轮车。这种交通工具通常是木制的，由牛、驴或马等役畜牵拉。这些役畜与一根长杆连在一起，然后这根长杆固定到车的前部。车辆的上部通常会用木条交叉做成笼子的形状。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻译</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>圣经中的车辆都是由役畜牵拉的，翻译者应避免使用任何由发动机驱动的车辆名称来翻译“车”。</p>\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/OAI-0066_cart_with_yoke_of_oxen.png\" alt=\"OAI-0066_cart_with_yoke_of_oxen\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\"> (Image generated by ChatGPT using OpenAI technology)</figcaption></figure>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:3\">NUM 7:3</a> ：希伯来文短语<em>‘eglothtsav</em> 在这里的意思不确定。大多数翻译者和解经家都认为这是一种类似“篷车”（“covered wagons”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised English Bible (1989)\">REB</abbr> ）的东西。篷车的样式和上面描述的车辆相似，但是有一块布盖住车辆里面的物品。这种车辆的形状可能很像陆龟或海龟，而希伯来文<em>tsav</em> 正是指这种动物。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:24\">EZK 23:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:10\">EZK 26:10</a> ：希伯来文<em>galgal</em> 的字面意思是“轮子”。在这两节经文的语境中，这个词显然是换喻，指有轮子的车。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Esd5:53\">1ES 5:53</a> ：在这节经文中，有些希腊文抄本作<em>chara</em> （“喜乐”），这是不合理的。有一份抄本作<em>karron</em> ，意指前文提到的“车辆”。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
